Figure Caption: XRD patterns of arc-melted TiZrNbTaMo alloy (a) several main peaks, (b) deconvoluted (111) peak using Lorentz function, and (c) deconvoluted (321) peak using Lorentz function.

Backscattering SEM images taken from as-polished cross-sections at (a) top and (b) middle parts of arc-melted TiZrNbTaMo HEA ingot, showing two phases with distinct morphologies and compositions, bcc1 (in light) and bcc2 (in dark).
Element mapping with EDX for each component in the TiZrNbTaMo HEA, showing elemental segregation in dendritic (bcc1) and interdendritic (bcc2) regions.
P-hcurves under nanoindentation for dendritic and interdendritic regions of the TiZrNbTaMo HEA, tested with a Berkovich indenter.
Compressive engineering stress-strain curves of several typical specimens of as-cast TiZrNbTaMo HEA, tested at room temperature.

SEM images taken from fracture surfaces of as-cast TiZrNbTaMo HEA subjected to compressive failure. (a) top-view of bottom surface, (b) low-magnification views of fracture surface, (c) zoom-in image of blocked area in (b), and (d), (e), (f) zoom-in image of area labeled as I, II, III in (c), respectively.
